other_tests.findings: Ill-defined 4.6 x 6.7 x 5.5 cm lesion superior to the expected location of the appendix, medial to the cecum, with some poorly defined T2 hyperintense spaces, mostly intermediate signal on T2 weighted images. Thickened, irregular, and enhancing periphery with linear enhancing foci likely representing thick septation. Trace free fluid in the right lower quadrant. Note that a discrete appendix is not identified.
